<br>
 <p>Antra Immortalis <BR> Member of the Phoenix Crusaders <BR> Arch Mage of Mithaniel Marr <BR> E. Marr Server<BR>Magelo: <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=142225">Antra</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulegyndarydoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Legynd Arydoc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/10/02 1:24:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3394.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: !</span><hr size=1> <br>
Wizards' damage is still underpar (exceptions raid situations and AE spells).  Sure, they can dump their bar to do insane damage,<br>
but their SUSTAINABLE rate of damage is still well below that of a hasted tank.  Given that wizards are all about damage,<br>
I'd like to see this class improved.  NOW, wizards get GREAT axp skills, which increase their damage substantially.  This is good on the one hand, in that they get a better benefit out of axp than some other classes, but it's sad on the other because they have to get axp just to be 'balanced'.  As someone who has played this<br>
class rather extensively now versus others, I do believe they are underpowered.  Mages are extremely useful, period, raids or soloing, so no complaints there.  Necros also are quite good, even though their raid role isn't so well-defined...they are just very powerful.<br>
Druids are a bit underpowered, imo; they need a way to contribute to the tank/yawn or tank/heal formula.  Right now, they cannot<br>
increase tank damage through haste, or adequately handle hard-hitting mobs (no slow, torpor, big heals).  I don't know what improvements should be made to the class, but a larger damage shield has been suggested as one possibility... a bigger heal as another.  In my opinion, healing doesn't fix the class.<br>
A big damage shield, however, is interesting, and might be a good solution.  Shamans are just fantastic...probably the best class combo in EQ for quality in soloing, 6-man grouping, AND raid situations.<br>
That leaves clerics, which got a huge boost in power with blessed armor of the risen and judgment, both great spells.  I would still like to see some better<br>
undead DOTs/nukes to give clerics a real soloing option (something on the order of druid dots but only affects undead and takes perhaps a bit more mana).  The real problem with some casting classes, imo,<br>
is that they are not desired in 6-man groups.  It's not that they are objectively weak (since many can solo so well); it is simply that those who would like to group with the class have trouble finding one.  legy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukerryndarkwater.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kerryn Darkwater</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1635<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/11/02 1:44:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3394.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: !</span><hr size=1> This is the case with a lot of classes.<br>
<br>
I'm kinda happy with my direction in life at the moment because us paladins have had some big upgrades over the last 6 months, but, if you remember a year ago when the class balancing talks started, Paladins asked for certain things to bring them in line with other classes.<br>
<br>
These were almost exclusively added as AA points and Verant have basically said &quot;there ya go&quot; whilst at the same point giving every other class an upgrade in the same way.<br>
<br>
