<br>
Ah hah. Your idea of a balanced wizard class is one which can sustain the same damage output as a hasted melee with good equipment, plus do insane damage by burning, plus root, snare, stun, invis, teleport, and so on?<br>
<br>
Interesting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udalamarndarkgem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dalamarn Darkgem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 333<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/11/02 4:15:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3394.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VI needs to withdraw head from ass</span><hr size=1> Ssetti said: <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> But then ... why should you?&quot; <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> The reason everyone should have them is because this is meant to balance casters out with meleers.  Meleers get their skills automatically.  As they level, their added combat skills kick in.  I guess no one has found a way to bullshlt their way around this fact and so they're just ignoring it.  At 50+, the combat modifiers increase at an insane rate.  Where are the comparitive changes to casters??? Oh yeah.. that's what this &quot;balance&quot; is about.  How is it balancing when the majority of the playerbase will not have these items.  The items that are supposed to equal out the classes.  <br>
<br>
As far as mage focus items, they're great, but very limited in use depending on your class.  They dont affect DOTs at all, and as a necro, only affect my undead nukes and lifetaps.  As our other nukes have a 1/2 sec stun component, or snare effect, or illusion as part of them, they are not affected by the mage focus items.  The casting haste item is really the only one worth a damn for my class (but I do LOVE it).  <br>
<br>
Until ALL casters have the changes (like ALL meleers do), then it isn't really balanced is it? <p><a href="http://members.aol.com/wvvetteman/images/dalonhorse1.jpg" target="_blank">
<img src="http://members.aol.com/wvvetteman/images/dalonhorse1.jpg" border="0" WIDTH=108 HEIGHT=222>
</a> <BR> ~Dalamarn Darkgem~ <BR>~Harbinger of Death~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ussetti.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ssetti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 130<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/11/02 10:49:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3394.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VI needs to withdraw head from ass</span><hr size=1> &quot;Meleers get their skills automatically. As they level, their added combat skills kick in.&quot;<br>
<br>
So, in fact, do your spells (sure, there are a few that are pretty difficult to get hold of, but these days the vast majority of spells are both common and cheap).<br>
<br>
Perhaps the issue here is the ambiguity of the word &quot;balance&quot;. The basic abilities of all the classes strike me as being pretty well-balanced already ... the big disparity is that melee gear can make its user orders of magnitude more effective, whereas caster gear doesn't actually make all that much difference. These focus items could be seen as an attempt to address that by introducing high-level caster items that are really worth having.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, that's just my perspective. Other people doubtless think that the basic class definitions are horribly wrong, and there's really no way to prove them right or wrong about this. Maybe Verant should have been more specific about the purpose of the focus items.<br>
